Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.54,0:00:10.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There should be another assault! \NDon't let your guard down!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.90,0:00:30.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.19,0:00:33.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong? Izuru, are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.89,0:00:38.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Red 5. I just... I just...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.33,0:00:48.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the heck did you just do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.15,0:00:49.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.13,0:00:52.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just saw something disturbing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.53,0:00:53.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.51,0:00:54.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.84,0:00:56.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like what? Was it a ghostie?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.68,0:00:57.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right! I need to give pursuit.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.10,0:01:01.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What gives? Why isn't it moving?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.02,0:01:03.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on, Izuru?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.39,0:01:05.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.52,0:01:06.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,During battle, I-
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.60,0:01:09.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Red 5, you are prohibited \Nfrom further communication.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.32,0:01:13.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must not tell anyone about \Nwhat you just witnessed.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.36,0:01:17.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Upon your return, come \Nreport to me immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.58,0:01:22.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.95,0:01:24.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru, what happened?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.46,0:01:26.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Respond, Izuru!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.91,0:01:30.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's working?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.01,0:01:41.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong with him now?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.11,0:01:43.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe he got an owie?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.31,0:01:46.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His unit may have taken some \Ndamage, but Izuru is fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.52,0:01:47.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, look!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.27,0:01:52.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All of the enemy vessels are \Npulling out of the battle zone?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.90,0:01:54.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean we won?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.90,0:01:56.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yay!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.55,0:01:58.17,Top Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We won! We won!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.87,0:02:00.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why? They had victory \Nin their grasp...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.17,0:02:01.48,Top Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was a piece of cake! Yay!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.76,0:03:49.40,Copy of Ep Title,,0000,0000,0000,,"Disclosure"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.16,0:03:52.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The entire enemy fleet is retreating!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.01,0:03:53.57,Top Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We will begin accepting \Ninjured onto our ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.45,0:03:53.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.57,0:03:54.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Commence a running fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.83,0:03:57.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we could, I would have \Nissued the orders already!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.55,0:04:03.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The tactical heavy laser system \Nhas been damaged beyond repair!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.91,0:04:06.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am unable to reach the \Nsquad that was guarding it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.09,0:04:08.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The convoy vessel, Stout, \Nis requesting help.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.03,0:04:09.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Likewise, the convoy vessel, \NShiloh, is also requesting help.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.65,0:04:11.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're also receiving distress signals
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.12,0:04:13.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,from ships in the first and second \Nlines of defense that are unable to move.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.49,0:04:16.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Earth's GDF Headquarters \Nare still on the line.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.32,0:04:19.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They would like a \Ndetailed damage report.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.20,0:04:28.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Purple 2 has boarded!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.52,0:04:29.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Both the unit and pilot are unharmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.43,0:04:35.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome back, Miss. You did wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.75,0:04:38.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kei!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.29,0:04:39.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay? Kei!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.04,0:04:40.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hang in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.71,0:04:42.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.34,0:04:45.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down, Kei. The battle is over now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.47,0:04:47.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're glad to see you made \Nit back safe and sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.51,0:04:49.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Team Rabbits fought valiantly out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.64,0:04:51.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're all very proud of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.26,0:04:54.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now leave the rest to us \Nand try to take it easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.06,0:04:56.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is Red 5?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.46,0:04:58.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Has Izuru made it back yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.69,0:04:59.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.77,0:05:01.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't heard one way or the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.40,0:05:04.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did something happen to Red 5?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.66,0:05:13.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doberman and Rabbits are the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.10,0:05:15.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,only squads that didn't \Nsuffer any casualties.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.65,0:05:18.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For them to survive that battle \Nroyal essentially unscathed,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.20,0:05:19.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,their units must be something else!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.17,0:05:21.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No kiddin'!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.34,0:05:24.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're the ones who assembled these \Npuppies and kept them up an' running!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.05,0:05:26.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way the \NWulgaru could touch 'em!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.72,0:05:28.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right. We owe it all to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.88,0:05:29.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for-
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.60,0:05:31.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.14,0:05:36.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not what you should \Nbe saying, you lame pilot!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.81,0:05:37.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wha-?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.43,0:05:40.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was that the best you could do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.23,0:05:42.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Watching you pissed me off!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.15,0:05:44.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.73,0:05:45.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Man, you suck!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.90,0:05:48.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time you're gonna get shot \Ndown and die if you keep this up!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.70,0:05:50.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that doesn't sit well \Nif you, train harder to-
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.74,0:05:51.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Watch what you say!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.96,0:05:53.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's all true!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.28,0:05:56.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let go of me, Papa! Let go, dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.64,0:05:58.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry about that \Nfoul mouth of hers.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.19,0:06:00.50,Top Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no reason to hold me back!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.73,0:06:00.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She must have inherited it from my wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.50,0:06:03.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just you wait, you...! \NYou...! You little...!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.91,0:06:03.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Believe it or not, she \Nwas worried about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.17,0:06:04.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't hold it against her.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.87,0:06:04.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get you, dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.55,0:06:08.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It-it's fine. After all, she's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.63,0:06:10.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You lame pilot!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.47,0:06:13.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They sure did a number on you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.26,0:06:15.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But in a way, you were lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.60,0:06:18.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it had gone any deeper, that would \Nhave been the end of you, Icchan.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.93,0:06:19.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Icchan?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.14,0:06:23.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't look like your transmission \Ncables or drives got damaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.61,0:06:26.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure that it suddenly \Nstopped responding to your orders?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.90,0:06:30.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. When I tried to pursue an \Nenemy unit, it wouldn't budge.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.78,0:06:33.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means it must have \Nbeen the JURIA-SYSTEM.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.53,0:06:36.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the only explanation \NI can come up with.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.66,0:06:39.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So the AHSMB tried to defend itself?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.00,0:06:41.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like it's gonna take a while
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.87,0:06:44.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for you to tame this bunking bronco.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.63,0:06:49.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That means I still haven't \Nmastered my unit, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.84,0:06:52.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You got into a dogfight \Nwith the enemy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.72,0:06:53.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was he like?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.72,0:06:56.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could you see his face?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.00,0:06:56.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or what he looked like?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.43,0:06:58.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.43,0:07:02.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, okay, stop! That's \Nenough chit-chat.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.84,0:07:05.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't the captain waiting? \NYou'd better run.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.48,0:07:06.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,R-right!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.90,0:07:08.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, please take good \Ncare of my unit for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.04,0:07:25.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then the enemy showed himself to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.08,0:07:26.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was surprised to see \Nthat he looked human.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.59,0:07:32.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He looked just like that \Nlady I met at the pool.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.97,0:07:33.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At the pool?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.15,0:07:35.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.33,0:07:37.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We aren't supposed to \Nremember our pasts,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.26,0:07:40.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but for some odd reason, \NI remembered her.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.98,0:07:41.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then-
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.10,0:07:44.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.44,0:07:45.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You may not mention this
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.89,0:07:50.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to anyone henceforth, not even \Nthe members of Team Rabbits.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.44,0:07:51.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've always found it strange!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.80,0:07:54.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who was that lady?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.46,0:07:56.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why is she the only person I remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.24,0:07:59.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Instructor, do you know what she-
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.81,0:08:04.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am no longer your instructor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.30,0:08:06.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm your captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.21,0:08:11.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will issue further orders later.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.12,0:08:12.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You may leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.02,0:08:12.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But-
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.67,0:08:13.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are dismissed!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.60,0:08:28.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I need to report to the commander...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.54,0:08:50.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"This duel was amusing."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.84,0:08:54.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Let us fight again, \Nprimitive creature!"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.92,0:08:58.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, he has identified \NRed 5 as his target?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.18,0:09:00.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Most likely.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.27,0:09:03.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never expected this to happen...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.02,0:09:07.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that it has come to this,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.31,0:09:09.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe it is necessary to enlighten \NTeam Rabbits of the situation,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.61,0:09:11.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,at least to a certain degree.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.42,0:09:15.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is quite likely that the \NWulgaru will go after them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.40,0:09:18.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We must psychologically prepare \Nthem for what is to come,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.62,0:09:21.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,although I consider \Ndoing so most cruel...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.15,0:09:33.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you worried about that young man?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.76,0:09:35.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is a given.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.46,0:09:40.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He may have forgotten about \Nme, but I still remember him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.30,0:09:44.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If only I could see that \Nhe is indeed well...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.10,0:09:47.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You may go near the \Nexam room if you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.31,0:09:51.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, you will not be permitted \Nto speak with him directly.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.72,0:10:13.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you always hang out in my room?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.29,0:10:14.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go sleep in your own rooms!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.96,0:10:17.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm too excited to sleep!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.41,0:10:21.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I'm by myself, I keep \Nthinking about that battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.26,0:10:25.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, we can see all of the \Nreturning ally ships from this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.86,0:10:41.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We were beaten like dogs, didn't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.82,0:10:45.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! But didn't we win?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.58,0:10:47.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Wulgaru ran away!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.91,0:10:51.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know why, but it's true \Nthat the enemy pulled back.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.84,0:10:55.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Regardless, Earth suffered \Nfar heavier losses.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.53,0:10:57.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Forty percent...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.59,0:11:00.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...of our forces were \Nliterally annihilated.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.96,0:11:06.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, something smells really good!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.31,0:11:08.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I lit an aroma candle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.77,0:11:10.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard they can have \Nsoothing properties.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.81,0:11:12.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.38,0:11:17.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what's keeping Izuru...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.63,0:11:19.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet quarantine is taking a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.94,0:11:23.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, they said his \Ncockpit got torn wide open.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.41,0:11:49.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't sleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.98,0:11:51.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Lame pilot."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.59,0:11:55.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I got called... \Nby a member of my pit crew.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.93,0:12:03.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I had done a better \Njob issuing orders,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.28,0:12:05.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the battle may have gone better.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.70,0:12:15.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If someone else had been the leader...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.33,0:12:18.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it had been him...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.56,0:12:21.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just maybe, more lives...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.48,0:12:23.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're overthinking things!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.00,0:12:25.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt anyone could have done better.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.47,0:12:31.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no way I could have handled it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.14,0:12:36.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, I'm not really sure how to put it,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.78,0:12:38.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I felt like I could \Nrely on you back there!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.94,0:12:43.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those words held a drop of salvation...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.05,0:12:51.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He really is taking forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.40,0:12:55.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's in the exam room, \Nright? I'll check on him!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.57,0:12:58.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They probably won't let you in!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.50,0:12:59.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll check anyway!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.74,0:13:24.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.45,0:13:26.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank goodness!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.28,0:13:29.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where have you been? What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.78,0:13:32.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.88,0:13:40.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, say something!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.58,0:13:41.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,K-Kei!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.63,0:13:46.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S-sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.27,0:14:09.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why...?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.28,0:14:11.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.70,0:14:12.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.69,0:14:16.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why? What is she doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.89,0:14:18.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please wait! Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.84,0:14:24.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go back. Please hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.19,0:14:28.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.20,0:14:59.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru, not gonna eat that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.12,0:15:02.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Nah, I'm not hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.83,0:15:04.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'll take it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.69,0:15:06.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The food is the only thing
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.16,0:15:08.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that's leveled up since \Nwe've moved to this base!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.12,0:15:08.75,Top Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.96,0:15:10.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? In regard to? It's so good!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.26,0:15:12.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I'd like to know!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.30,0:15:13.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You two've been acting \Nstrange since last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.72,0:15:15.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the heck happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.89,0:15:23.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're all dead? That's horrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.56,0:15:27.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet it'll take a while \Nto regroup our forces.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.98,0:15:30.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like we'll be \Nabandoning Ceres Base.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.86,0:15:34.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently the higher-ups have \Nabsolutely no idea what to do next.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.57,0:15:36.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is going to happen to us?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.66,0:15:40.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The big wigs are already pointing \Ntheir fingers at each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.32,0:15:44.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It won't be long before this base \Nis overridden with injured soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.88,0:15:47.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If they strike again now...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.50,0:15:49.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We wouldn't last a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.59,0:15:53.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong? You look so glum!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.93,0:15:55.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the lunch lady!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.26,0:15:56.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.43,0:15:58.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you come after me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.93,0:16:00.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dang, that's awe-
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.65,0:16:05.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I got reassigned shortly after you left.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.05,0:16:07.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They said that this base \Nwas a bit understaffed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.77,0:16:11.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know it's been crazy \Nsince you arrived,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.85,0:16:14.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but don't let one lost battle \Nget you down in the dumps!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.82,0:16:17.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the heroes who \Nsaved Earth, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.24,0:16:19.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're heroes?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.44,0:16:20.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We are?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.74,0:16:22.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what the news keeps calling you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.83,0:16:25.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yesterday's battle was a \Nhuge victory for Earth!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.60,0:16:27.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It says that Team Rabbits \Nis a group of young heroes
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.47,0:16:29.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who magnificently repelled \Nthe flood of enemy ships!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.23,0:16:33.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really? So we were a big help after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.95,0:16:35.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is just a repeat of last time!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.58,0:16:40.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They need to throw out some \Nheroes whenever we lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.43,0:16:46.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like I said, don't look so glum!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.10,0:16:48.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Asagi! You ought to eat more.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.62,0:16:50.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Want me to bring you seconds?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.57,0:16:53.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, my stomach is starting \Nto hurt again...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.99,0:16:55.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,May we join you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.59,0:16:58.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, sure. Feel free.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.08,0:17:01.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you the operators...?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.40,0:17:05.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am Communications Manager \NSiegfried von Westernach.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.22,0:17:08.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Guiliano Visconti.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.59,0:17:11.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, where is my milk?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.17,0:17:11.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.09,0:17:14.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,R-right! Just one moment please.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.99,0:17:16.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't handle second tier studs!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.83,0:17:19.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me for being third tier!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.64,0:17:21.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for interrupting your meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.47,0:17:24.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We always talk over the monitor,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.03,0:17:26.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so we were hoping to \Nspeak with you in person.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.77,0:17:31.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! I love octopus and squid, \Nespecially their pickled innards!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.98,0:17:34.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How long do you expect it to \Ntake to reorganize the fleet?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.32,0:17:36.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't say.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.39,0:17:38.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As it stands now, we don't even know
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.16,0:17:39.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the exact scale of our losses.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.07,0:17:42.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But not all of the news is bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.53,0:17:43.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We learned that your AHSMB
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.86,0:17:46.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,units are able to fight \Non par with the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.04,0:17:51.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I imagine we'll build upon your \NAHSMB team and regroup around that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.09,0:17:52.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if you flip it around,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.88,0:17:55.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the AHSMB units were the only \Nthing doing any damage, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.70,0:17:56.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.96,0:17:59.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They should already be working on \Nincreasing AHSMB unit production.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.97,0:18:02.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Although even we aren't \Nprivy to the details.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.35,0:18:05.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tamaki, this is important! \NAre you paying attention?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.21,0:18:09.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I can't pick one at \Nthe drop of a hat!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.02,0:18:11.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't, I can't, I can't! I just can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.31,0:18:12.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've got your hands full, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.83,0:18:14.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.52,0:18:18.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about I treat everyone to dessert?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.99,0:18:20.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please order anything you like!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.99,0:18:23.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'll take a space-sized \NStar Rose Parfait!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.62,0:18:25.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,FRUIT PARFAIT: LIMITED TIME ONLY \NSTAR ROSE PARFAIT: SPACE SIZE
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.86,0:18:32.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was fast...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.92,0:18:36.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone from Team Rabbits!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.59,0:18:38.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got a message \Nfrom Captain Suzukaze!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.99,0:18:40.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For all of us?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.22,0:18:43.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?! But I was just \Nabout to have dessert!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.85,0:18:45.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She needs you pronto!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.43,0:18:49.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Team Rabbits is to meet in \NOperating Room No. 7 immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.02,0:18:51.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's all!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.58,0:19:01.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At ease!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.20,0:19:08.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As you are aware, the GDF suffered \Nheavy losses in the Battle of Ceres.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.87,0:19:11.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Henceforth, I imagine the AHSMB \Nteams, starting with Team Rabbits,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.99,0:19:13.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,will be sent on an increasing \Nnumber of missions.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.17,0:19:16.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In preparation for the upcoming battles,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.05,0:19:19.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have decided to divulge certain \Ninformation with you in advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.73,0:19:24.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, everything said here is of \Nthe utmost confidential of nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.25,0:19:26.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you tell anyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.23,0:19:33.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll meet the firing squad?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.99,0:19:35.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll start with this video.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.82,0:19:40.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wasn't I supposed to keep this a secret?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.65,0:19:43.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll go over it in a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.66,0:19:46.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the heck? We're fighting humans?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.66,0:19:48.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's saying something to Izuru...!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.38,0:19:50.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He isn't human.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.33,0:19:55.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He may resemble us, but he is \Na completely different species.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.46,0:19:57.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He looks damn nasty!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.88,0:19:59.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really? I think he's cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.21,0:20:02.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's the enemy! The enemy!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.42,0:20:04.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you like anyone that looks cool?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.80,0:20:06.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't say that...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.64,0:20:13.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you might be right!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.60,0:20:15.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this what you were referring to?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.61,0:20:21.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not just his appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.36,0:20:23.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His fighter moves a lot \Nlike our AHSMB units.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.29,0:20:29.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly! Our AHSMBs \Nutilize their technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.15,0:20:34.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once, two pieces of information were \Nleaked through a certain route.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.42,0:20:38.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The first was that the Wulgaru \Nwere preparing to invade Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.38,0:20:41.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The second was the basic technology \Nbehind the AHSMB units.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.45,0:20:42.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was the intel.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.47,0:20:45.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The AHSMBs that Team Rabbits currently
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.92,0:20:48.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,pilot were developed using \Nthat leaked technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.36,0:20:53.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So we've been piloting Wulgaru fighters?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.18,0:20:58.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Their basic plans may hail \Nfrom Wulgaru origins,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.40,0:21:01.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but we are the ones who adapted \Nthem for human pilots.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.72,0:21:05.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The JURIA-SYSTEM was also developed \Nby a member of the MJP.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.52,0:21:12.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.12,0:21:19.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How did that leaked information \Nget to Earth to begin with?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.00,0:21:22.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How did we find out \Nthat the Wulgaru were
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.11,0:21:23.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,after Earth and learn \Nhow the AHSMB work?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.21,0:21:28.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Wulgaru defector delivered \Nthe information to Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.26,0:21:30.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A defector...?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.86,0:21:33.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will let her explain \Nthe situation in detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.23,0:21:38.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's you...!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.28,0:21:47.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So we meet again.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.94,0:23:55.95,Copy of Ep Title,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Hunter and the Hunted"
